                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14461301" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2005 04:52:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is not true in general:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;list = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1,2,3,4,5&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
int[] array = list.toArray([] as int[])&lt;br/&gt;
assert array.class.name == &quot;[I&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but it does not work for your example. Maybe it&apos;s because the method is static&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461420" author="guillaume" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2005 06:04:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact, this is not a bug, but rather an error in that script.&lt;br/&gt;
Runtime.getRuntime.exec() should be used instead of Runtime.exec(), since (as Kim spotted) exec() is an instance method of Runtime, not a static method.&lt;br/&gt;
So the problem isn&apos;t about invoking a method with an array as parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461188" author="phkim" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2005 22:29:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be reopened since it does not work on jsr-03.&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Won;t fix&quot; is different from &quot;Fixed&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461302" author="phkim" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2005 22:31:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been fixed with&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/groovy/groovy-core?cs=MAIN:phk:20050818113623&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/groovy/groovy-core?cs=MAIN:phk:20050818113623&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461440" author="phkim" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2005 22:35:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The title &quot;Problem invoking a method with arrays as arguments&quot; should be changed as&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Support cmdString.execute(envpArray, workDir)&quot; in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
